\chapter{Learning Roadmap}\label{ch:roadmap}

\paragraph{Overview.}
This chapter provides a structured 9-week self-study plan covering the full spectrum of knowledge graph topics --- from graph theory fundamentals to cutting-edge research. Each week includes reading, practice exercises, and project work.

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Phase 1: Foundations (Weeks 1--3)}\label{sec:phase1}

\begin{description}
	\item[Week 1: Graph theory and RDF basics.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:graph-theory} of this book + Diestel Chapters 1--3.
		      \item Practice: Build a small RDF graph with rdflib in Python.
		      \item Project: Model your personal music library as RDF triples using Turtle syntax.
		      \item Milestone: Load, query, and manipulate an RDF graph of $>$100 triples.
	      \end{itemize}

	\item[Week 2: SPARQL querying.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:querying}, Sections~\ref{sec:sparql} and~\ref{sec:query-opt}.
		      \item Practice: Query Wikidata via its public SPARQL endpoint (query.wikidata.org).
		      \item Project: Write 10 SPARQL queries of increasing complexity (1-hop $\to$ 3-hop with FILTER).
		      \item Milestone: Retrieve multi-hop paths from a public KG.
	      \end{itemize}

	\item[Week 3: Ontology design.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:ontologies}.
		      \item Practice: Model a small domain (e.g., university) in Protege with OWL 2 axioms.
		      \item Project: Add disjointness, cardinality restrictions, and a transitive property. Run the HermiT reasoner.
		      \item Milestone: Design and validate an OWL ontology with 10+ classes and 5+ object properties.
	      \end{itemize}
\end{description}

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Phase 2: Construction and Querying (Weeks 4--5)}\label{sec:phase2}

\begin{description}
	\item[Week 4: KG construction pipeline.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:construction}.
		      \item Practice: Run spaCy NER on Wikipedia text. Extract entities and relations.
		      \item Project: Build an end-to-end pipeline: text $\to$ NER $\to$ RE $\to$ entity linking $\to$ RDF store.
		      \item Milestone: Construct a KG of 500+ triples from unstructured text.
	      \end{itemize}

	\item[Week 5: Neo4j and Cypher.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:querying}, Section~\ref{sec:cypher}.
		      \item Practice: Install Neo4j (local or Docker). Load the Week 4 KG.
		      \item Project: Write 10 Cypher queries: MATCH, WHERE, variable-length paths, shortestPath, aggregation.
		      \item Milestone: Query a property graph database with Cypher.
	      \end{itemize}
\end{description}

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Phase 3: ML Integration (Weeks 6--7)}\label{sec:phase3}

\begin{description}
	\item[Week 6: KG embeddings.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:embeddings}.
		      \item Practice: Train TransE and RotatE on FB15k-237 using PyKEEN.
		      \item Project: Evaluate link prediction performance. Compare MRR and Hits@10 across models.
		      \item Milestone: Reproduce a published KG embedding result.
	      \end{itemize}

	\item[Week 7: Graph Neural Networks.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:gnns}.
		      \item Practice: Implement GCN and GAT layers in PyTorch Geometric.
		      \item Project: Train a GNN for node classification on a citation network (Cora, PubMed).
		      \item Milestone: Achieve $>$80\% accuracy on Cora node classification.
	      \end{itemize}
\end{description}

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Phase 4: LLM Integration and Research (Weeks 8--9)}\label{sec:phase4}

\begin{description}
	\item[Week 8: GraphRAG.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:graphrag}.
		      \item Practice: Build a simple GraphRAG pipeline with Neo4j + LLM (OpenAI or local).
		      \item Project: Compare standard RAG vs.\ GraphRAG on 10 multi-hop questions.
		      \item Milestone: GraphRAG pipeline answering multi-hop questions correctly.
	      \end{itemize}

	\item[Week 9: Constrained decoding and KGQA.]
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Read: Chapter~\ref{ch:kgqa}.
		      \item Practice: Implement a GCR-style trie for path-constrained decoding.
		      \item Project: Run the DCA-Trie codebase on WebQSP. Compare Hits@1 with the GCR baseline.
		      \item Milestone: Reproduce a constrained decoding result and analyse the pruning statistics.
	      \end{itemize}
\end{description}

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Weekly Commitment}\label{sec:commitment}

\begin{table}[h]
	\centering
	\caption{Estimated weekly time commitment}
	\label{tab:commitment}
	\begin{tabular}{lc}
		\toprule
		Activity           & Hours \\
		\midrule
		Reading            & 3--4  \\
		Practice exercises & 3--4  \\
		Project work       & 4--6  \\
		\bottomrule
	\end{tabular}
\end{table}

Total: 10--14 hours/week. Learners with stronger backgrounds may complete Phases 1--2 in 2 weeks and dedicate more time to Phases 3--4.

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Advanced Extensions}\label{sec:extensions}

After completing the 9-week plan:
\begin{enumerate}
	\item \textbf{Research paper reproduction:} Pick a paper from Chapter~\ref{ch:advanced} and reproduce its results.
	\item \textbf{Novel contribution:} Identify a limitation in DCA-Trie (e.g., the type oracle could be extended with OWL reasoning) and implement an improvement.
	\item \textbf{Production deployment:} Deploy a GraphRAG system with real data (company documents, customer support tickets).
\end{enumerate}

