	Wikidata              & $\sim$1.5B statements       & General        & \url{https://query.wikidata.org/}                                    \\
	DBpedia               & $\sim$40M entities          & Wikipedia      & \url{https://www.dbpedia.org/}                                       \\
	YAGO                  & $\sim$10M entities          & General        & \url{https://yago-knowledge.org/}                                    \\
	ConceptNet            & $\sim$8M nodes              & Commonsense    & \url{https://conceptnet.io/}                                         \\
	Freebase (deprecated) & $\sim$50M entities          & General        & \url{https://developers.google.com/freebase}                         \\
	FB15k-237             & 15K entities, 237 relations & KGQA benchmark & \url{https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=52312} \\
	WN18RR                & 41K entities, 11 relations  & KGQA benchmark & \url{https://github.com/TimDettmers/ConvE}                           \\
	WebQSP                & 4,737 questions             & KGQA           & \url{https://github.com/kelvinguu/webqsp}                            \\
	ComplexWebQuestions   & 34,689 questions            & KGQA           & \url{https://github.com/IBM/ComplexWebQuestions}                     \\
\end{longtable}

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Conferences and Venues}\label{sec:res-venues}

\begin{description}
	\item[ICML / NeurIPS / ICLR:] Primary ML venues; KG embedding and GNN papers.
	\item[ACL / EMNLP / NAACL:] NLP + KG integration; KGQA, GraphRAG.
	\item[ISWC (International Semantic Web Conference):] Core KG venue; ontologies, SPARQL, RDF.
	\item[WWW / KDD:] Applied KG papers; construction, search, industrial systems.
	\item[AKBC (Automated Knowledge Base Construction):] Focused on KG construction.
\end{description}

% ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Reproduction Checklist}\label{sec:res-checklist}

When reproducing a KG paper:
\begin{enumerate}
	\item Ensure you have the exact dataset split used in the paper.
	\item Check the evaluation protocol: filtered or unfiltered? Raw or standardised?
	\item Verify the hyperparameters (embedding dimension $d$, learning rate, batch size, number of negative samples).
	\item Run 5 random seeds and report mean $\pm$ std.
	\item Compare against published numbers from the \emph{same} test set.
\end{enumerate}

